York removes last of its kind historical artifact</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KKxq2bL</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nK6qMQ1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>New York City's LAST public pay-phone booth, at 50th and 7th has been removed.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KKxq2bL</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Igotfourbedrats]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>1 year and 110lbs ago</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/cBvV3Mx</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/g2hREfb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That messy bathroom is NOT mine!

Edit:
So to answer some questions. I was at my cousin's house and encouraged to share my weight loss. I have been so embarrassed for so long about how I let myself go, but she's right. I should be proud of myself and just move forward. She has a full length mirror. I don't.

I had the gastric sleeve surgery last year. And before I anybody decides to comment about how they think that's cheating, please take into consideration that I was so desperate to lose weight, weight that I had been struggling with for years, weight that started because of major depression and ended up in a vicious cycle of depression, stress-eating, and weight gain, that my last resort was a major abdominal surgery that could potentially kill me or make me miserable for the rest of my life. My weight got to the point that I could no longer move without my joints being incredibly painful. My health was severely declining. I was sick all the time. Far from healthy. The weight loss started to fall off quickly, but the first 30-40 lbs is mostly water weight. It was HARD to stick to the post surgery diet, but I did. It's like my body got a reset button. I practice mindful eating. I have pretty much cut added sugar out of my diet and I watch my carb intake. I eat 3 times a day, but they're normal sized meals (3-4 ounces of meat, a serving of veggies...far from the huge meals we're all used to that is overeating). I have lost my taste for pasta and breads. In fact, they make me feel ill so I don't really eat them because of that. Too much sugar makes me ill. Too much dairy makes me ill. So all of those have been cut to a bare minimum just because I don't like the way I feel after I've consumed it. I treat myself to an iced latte every day (I'm a basic bitch), but I make my own and I use unsweetened original almond milk and sugar free coffee syrups. That pretty much keeps my sweet tooth at bay. I prep my meals because I know that if I don't, I'll eat like shit. When I wake up in the morning and I'm getting ready for the day, I tell myself out loud what my food goals for the day is (it's usually no sugar and stay hydrated). I make promises to myself and I keep them. I could exercise more, but I hate the gym so I stay more active at work and outdoors (I don't sit on my ass at work and I love kayaking and hiking). It's a lot of hard work and a lot of reminding myself to treat my body well. I still have a long way to go, but slow and steady wins the race.

This weight loss has not only improved my health, but it has improved my confidence and the way that I view myself. I have a better relationship with food. I'm much more socially active and I'm learning to love myself again. It is honestly the best decision I've ever made for my body.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cBvV3Mx</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MimicOctopi]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>and so it begins...</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/p5zTQCV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/usexuzH.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/p5zTQCV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[fulcrims]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My Catwoman Cosplay</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/N0wa8tW</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rnWPEwC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>SnarkyJayCosplay here with my new Catwoman cosplay. This one’s inspired mostly by Clay Mann and Joelle Jones (for the photos without the cowl).</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XeJ5GOl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I thought of the Batmilk bottle myself and it was such a huge hit at Megacon!
